content.description: Start left hand on good edge and right hand on pinch rail. Using some tensiony heel hooks and compression, make huge moves up to the lip then up and over.
content.protection: A few pads help because the landing is jumbled.

content.description: Super proud!  Stand start with steep arete and gain sloper.  Toss out right to good hold and hike up to small crimps above the lip.  Finish move is super committing.   A sit start should be added for full value and added difficulty, but the holds were too wet for us to try.
content.location: This problem is on the middle of boulder with Impossiproject to the left.  The Prow is up hill and right about 20ft.

content.description:
Start left hand on good ledge and jump for right hand edge.  Get your feet on and move up boulder with a big cross-over move to a jug.  Powerful moves and props to Aaron for this contribution. 

  Starting lower with both hand below is still an awesome open project.
content.location: Line just left of Tunder Tighs.

content.description: From bellow steep bulge, start on large ledge and gain upper section of bulge.  Top-out.  Super cool!
content.location: If at Massive Vertigo hike downhill and right for approx. 50-75 feet.  Looking right(south) you should see this large feature.  Or right behind the Roof Traverse Project.

content.description: Start the same as "Tunder Tighs" and climb directly up the face with a small pit underneath you..  Formerly the "Big Boy Project"
content.location: The prow boulder, same start as "Tunder Tighs"

content.description: Climb starts in pit on good side pull with left hand and good right hand. Harder first couple moves then a pumpy arete. V3 start out of the pit and just do the arete.
Start hands low in horizontal break, up and over bulge to slab on small holds to topout.
content.protection: Pads (3+ ideal), not a good solo landing.
content.location: Just to right of The Prow.

content.description: Start underneath the arete with left hand on a toothlike hold and right on a pinch undercling.  Climb the arete with balance, gain the obvious holds on the face and top out.  This is also on here as the impossiproject.
content.protection: A few pads and a spot.
content.location: On big Boulder right below Tunder Tighs.  Easiest to leave tumbled rock trail 60 feet north of the bottom of the prominent slant talus field on the west bluff.  Only a few minute walk above trail.

content.description: Goes up the right side of the "Hipsters V5" boulder. Start on the juggy sidepulls and get a heel hook up right. Power straight up through a series of jugs/slopers to top it out.  Thuggy!
content.location: First large boulder straight down the talus field from Tunder Tighs...problem starts to the right of "The Hipsters V5"

content.description: Start as per Tunder Tighs, finish on Full Moon rising.  If you use the jugs as per Tunder Tighs to finish, you have officially cheated. Mantle it out..
Start sitting, left hand on the blunt arête, right on an undercling pinch with a definitive thumb catch. Go up and right to mantle, and finish with an easy slab.
content.location: Just below Tunder Tighs on the Remos Sacrifice Boulder.  This problem starts right below Remo's Sacrifice.  To get to the Massive Vertigo area walk straight up into the woods 100 feet south of the Nancy j Holdt bench.

content.description: Start low on the arete and climb up and out slab.
content.location: Just left(south) of the Prow Project.  Downhill and south of Massive Vertigo by approx. 50-75ft.

content.description: The central boulder in a small cluster of wooded boulders.
